c({"name": "jQuery.Model.prototype.attr", "params": {"attribute": {"description": "<p>the attribute you want to set or get</p>", "type": "String", "optional": false, "order": 0, "name": "attribute"}, "value": {"description": "<p>value the value you want to set.</p>", "type": "String|Number|Boolean", "optional": true, "order": 1, "name": "value"}, "success": {"description": "<p>an optional success callback. <br />\n   This gets called if the attribute was successful.</p>", "type": "Function", "optional": true, "order": 2, "name": "success"}, "error": {"description": "<p>an optional success callback. <br />\n   The error function is called with validation errors.</p>", "type": "Function", "optional": true, "order": 3, "name": "error"}}, "ret": {"type": "undefined", "description": ""}, "type": "function", "parents": ["jQuery.Model.prototype"], "comment": "<p>Gets or sets an attribute on the model using setters and \ngetters if available.</p>\n\n<pre><code class='javascript'>$.Model(\"Recipe\")\nvar recipe = new Recipe();\nrecipe.attr(\"foo\",\"bar\")\nrecipe.foo //-> \"bar\"\nrecipe.attr(\"foo\") //-> \"bar\"</code></pre>\n\n<h2>Setters</h2>\n\n<p>If you add a set<i>AttributeName</i> method on your model,\nit will be used to set the value.  The set method is called\nwith the value and is expected to return the converted value.</p>\n\n<pre><code class='javascript'>$.Model(\"Recipe\",{\n  setCreatedAt : function(raw){\n    return Date.parse(raw)\n  }\n})\nvar recipe = new Recipe();\nrecipe.attr(\"createdAt\",\"Dec 25, 1995\")\nrecipe.createAt //-> Date</code></pre>\n\n<h2>Asynchronous Setters</h2>\n\n<p>Sometimes, you want to perform an ajax request when \nyou set a property.  You can do this with setters too.</p>\n\n<p>To do this, your setter should return undefined and\ncall success with the converted value.  For example:</p>\n\n<pre><code class='javascript'>$.Model(\"Recipe\",{\n  setTitle : function(title, success, error){\n    $.post(\n      \"recipe/update/\"+this.id+\"/title\",\n      title,\n      function(){\n        success(title);\n      },\n      \"json\")\n  }\n})\n\nrecipe.attr(\"title\",\"fish\")</code></pre>\n\n<h2>Events</h2>\n\n<p>When you use attr, it can also trigger events.  This is\ncovered in [$.Model.prototype.bind].</p>", "src": "jquery/model/model.js", "line": 1256, "children": []})